The paper discusses a method for stealing knowledge from deep neural networks, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the use of neural networks and their architecture, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves generating composite images, which is a technique used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of student networks to mimic the mentor network, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of large datasets, which is a common topic in data science (cs.DS).
